<H1 class=3D"top">Configuring Deployment</H1>
<P>        Some PowerShell scripts have been added to your project to =
configure=20
and        launch your worker. These may be edited freely to customize =
your     =20
  deployment.     </P>
<P>        To change the version of Python your worker should run with, =
set the =20
       <CODE>PYTHON</CODE> property in the =
<CODE>ServiceDefinition.csdef</CODE> =20
      file in your cloud project. See =
<CODE>ConfigureCloudService.ps1</CODE>    =20
   for more details.     </P>
<P>        To install packages using pip, update the=20
<CODE>requirements.txt</CODE>        file in the root directory of your =
project.=20
The PowerShell script will        install packages listed in it on =
deployment.  =20
  </P>
<P>        To set <CODE>PYTHONPATH</CODE> (or equivalent) before running =
the    =20
   worker, add the environment variable to your        =20
<CODE>ServiceDefinition.csdef</CODE>.     </P>
<P>        To specify the script to run and any arguments, modify the =
command=20
line        in <CODE>ServiceDefinition.csdef</CODE>. The startup file =
and debug =20
       options in your local project do not automatically transfer to =
the       =20
deployed service.     </P>
<H1>Troubleshooting Deployment</H1>
<P>If your worker role does not behave correctly after deployment, check =
the=20
following:</P>
<OL>
  <LI>
  <P>Your Python project includes a bin\ folder with (at least):</P>
  <UL>
    <LI><CODE>ConfigureCloudService.ps1</CODE></LI>
    <LI><CODE>LaunchWorker.ps1</CODE></LI>
    <LI><CODE>ps.cmd</CODE></LI></UL></LI>
  <LI>Your Cloud project references those files from the service=20
definition.</LI>
  <LI>Your Python project includes a <CODE>requirements.txt</CODE> file =
listing=20
  all dependencies.</LI>
  <LI>
  <P>Enable Remote Desktop on your Cloud Service and investigate the log =

  files.</P>
  <P>                Logs for <CODE>ConfigureCloudService.ps1</CODE> and =
       =20
          <CODE>LaunchWorker.ps1</CODE> are stored in the following path =
       =20
         on the machine instance:             </P>
  <UL>
    =
<LI><CODE>C:\Resources\Directory\%RoleId%.DiagnosticStore\LogFiles</CODE>=
</LI></UL>
  <P>                Currently, the <CODE>LaunchWorker.ps1</CODE> log is =
the=20
  only way                to view output or errors displayed by your =
Python=20
  program.             </P></LI>
  <LI>            Start a discussion at             <A =
href=3D"http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=3D293415">our=20
  discussion forum</A>            for further help.         </LI></OL>
